synonyms.synonym: Tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 2

protein.general_function: Involved in tumor necrosis factor receptor binding
protein.specific_function: Cytokine that binds to TNFRSF1A/TNFR1 and TNFRSF1B/TNFBR. It is mainly secreted by macrophages and can induce cell death of certain tumor cell lines. It is potent pyrogen causing fever by direct action or by stimulation of interleukin-1 secretion and is implicated in the induction of cachexia, Under certain conditions it can stimulate cell proliferation and induce cell differentiation

go_class.description: tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily binding
